<subSubSection id="33220FC7AD12AA756F7C6789646546D5" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="26E647E7F1343CA570682AC5905BFC1F" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="5134E891E1C11278A95A56C0423B8E08" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus Myers 1932</taxonomicName>
: 159-162 (original description, type species: 
<taxonomicName id="063C0AD923C5446AE4087B790E720A3B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8DF8C2F2-A5F1-4548-BC19-AD4E00BDC5AB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus transilis Myers 1932:160" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="transilis">A. transilis Myers</taxonomicName>
, by original designation, based on single specimen). Hoedeman 1961: 89-91 (based on head scale patterns, 
<taxonomicName id="1B98A71D2C947E53B67ADEB744F3A49E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
put in separate subfamily from 
<taxonomicName id="27025048CE302EFAEEA474045692FCB5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
). Weitzman and Wourms 1967: 89-100 (generic characters discussed, validity of 
<taxonomicName id="11098CC4D3E50B924E7E02C68F28CF76" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="04CF7DFE482FA81CC1A04B7DDD7AF677" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="05CAC7A13CE225A475663D2CA1E2D583" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EF0F634C-4A82-4B33-86D6-31A498C4DB7C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Pterolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pterolebias Garman 1895:141" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pterolebias</taxonomicName>
is doubted). Vaz-Ferreira and Sierra de Soriano 1972: 38-40 (attempt to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="B480E7662E97376D7C948BE0BCC09794" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0B596E925C5BFFFCE780395855A9DC2D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
based on neuromast and lateral pore patterns, caudal and pelvic-fin morphology). Thomerson 1979: (comments on generic name). Elder Jr. et al. 1991: (karyotypes, comments on generic names). Costa 1990: (based primarily on osteological and meristic characters, 
<taxonomicName id="1C62CE0FACA7870179C1E0D81461B621" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
placed into synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="1922A636F895C932665DD720C4951CB3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
). Costa 1998: (
<taxonomicName id="2D6ACB2ED65FA2FFBB836F7D9D56301F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
revalidated but without explanation). Huber 1999: (morphometric relationships to other rivulin genera). Hrbek and Larson 1999: (phylogeny based on mitochondrial DNA data). Murphy et al. 1999: (phylogeny based on mitochondrial DNA data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F62E6EF73C1C172B66C0F70CA562F28B" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9D63221D93CBB24DFAC13717ED255655" pageNumber="12">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="E3D99C0419950C339F928F969784C2C9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
are Neotropical, northern South American, annual rivulid fishes that are distinguished from all new world rivulids except 
<taxonomicName id="A2237BE29D5DA829D662FADEEA70703A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
in having at least the basal 45% of the caudal fin scaled. They differ from the closely related genus 
<taxonomicName id="897F7358008FB523F9D28B68E0333C7E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 4) in having: more dorsal rays, usually 14 or more (range 12-18) vs. 13 or fewer (range 9-14); a longer dorsal fin base, more than 16% SL (12-25%) vs. less than 16% (10-18%); more lateral scales, usually 32 or more (28-38) vs. 32 or fewer (27-33); and more transverse scales, usually 11 or more (9-16) vs. usually 10 or less (8-11). Many males of 
<taxonomicName id="2DBC8BAE09386ECFA3BC34C2F28BD8D1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevis">R. brevis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A13276B9635820846189F0A318827218" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculipinnis">R. maculipinnis</taxonomicName>
have a dark blotch around white spots on the dorsal fin, a pattern never seen in 
<taxonomicName id="2BAD1C5DE9860B1C60079125300E348D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
, which never has white spots on the dorsal fin of males. The anal and genital papillae are usually heavily pigmented in 
<taxonomicName id="E56CD5BC8DCCAEAFF7BDD11E4C714BC8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
but only lightly pigmented or unpigmented in 
<taxonomicName id="3F1606FE7BCB392F42CF73A3A2634035" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F12E2023-61ED-419A-BF66-AB71508F9A02" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rachovia Myers 1927:119" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rachovia</taxonomicName>
and other new world rivulids from northern South America.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BFBE08C84D271AEF255E83A90AFBD2E2">
<paragraph id="81E6925069320208716904D0565CB8C1" pageNumber="12">
FIGURE 4. Photo of a male 
<taxonomicName id="38841515E8DBBDA40F3DA64EE72BD63E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rachovia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculipinnis">Rachovia maculipinnis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C512BB4397E4CA2F535F48FF4FC3DC43" lastPageNumber="13" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="A798F9AEEC5B8767EAFE6997EA30679C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A12D02B2-18D2-450F-B6ED-A28984BAD110" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Austrofundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Austrofundulus Myers 1932:159" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Austrofundulus</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="D1C5E67F0D56595407E8BFFEA3ED03C2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:79CEE90A-5FE1-406E-BE38-5DF8C249CD32" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Terranatos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Terranatos Taphorn &amp; Thomerson 1978:384" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Terranatos</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 5) in having: shorter fins, the dorsal fin less than 55% SL (range 23-47%) in males, and less than 40% SL (range 
<pageStartToken id="A602C57841F43525B504A4C97668B206" pageNumber="13">22</pageStartToken>
-40%) in females, versus more than 55% (55-124%) and more than 37% (37-47%) in males and females of 
<taxonomicName id="2B917AE461A05AEE7C540DDC454AD621" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:79CEE90A-5FE1-406E-BE38-5DF8C249CD32" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Terranatos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Terranatos Taphorn &amp; Thomerson 1978:384" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Terranatos</taxonomicName>
, respectively; caudal fin scaled for more than one third of its length vs. unscaled except at base; female without extensions of caudal fin rays vs. filamentous rays on the dorsal and ventral margins; maximum standard length more than 30 mm vs. less than 30 mm SL; anal actinosts articulated with hemal spines rather than ribs.
</paragraph>
